definition: People are classified as employed if during the survey reference week, they meet ANY of the following criteria: 1. Worked at least 1 hour as paid employee, 2. Worked at least 1 hour in own business (self-employed), 3. Temporarily absent from job, whether or not they were paid for time off, 4. Worked without pay for a minimum of 15 hours in family owned business.
